        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 25 at 2:12PM CST by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 212 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Low Gap, or 14 miles south of Tuscaloosa, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Centreville, Vance, Eoline, Low Gap, Duncanville, Pearson, Harmon,
Phipps, and Hagler.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 600 PM CST for central and
west central Alabama.</instruction>
